## Style Mechanism Map (what each tool writes to)

| Tool | Mechanism | Units |
|---|---|---|
| `set_background` | `props.className` (bg-[color] class) + strips `style.backgroundColor` | color string |
| `set_text_color` | `props.className` (text-* class) | color token / hex |
| `set_typography` | `props.className` (Tailwind text-* font-* etc.) | Tailwind tokens |
| `set_border` | `props.className` (border-* rounded-* classes) | Tailwind tokens |
| `set_shadow` | `props.className` (shadow-* class) | Tailwind tokens |
| `set_opacity` | `style.opacity` (0–1 float) | 0–100 input → divided by 100 |
| `set_spacing` | `props.className` as arbitrary-value classes (pt-[Npx], gap-[Npx], etc.) + strips `style.*` | pixels |
| `set_size` | `props.className` for all values: width/height modes + max-w-[Npx], min-w-[Npx], etc. + strips `style.*`; `px:N` double-writes class AND `style.*` | pixels / mode strings |
| `set_position` | `props.className` for position/zIndex + top-[Npx]/right-[Npx]/etc. for inset + strips `style.*` | pixels for inset |
| `set_transform` | `style.transform` for rotate; `props.className` for flip/cursor/overflow/self | degrees for rotate |
| `set_layout` | `props.className` for direction/align/justify + gap-[Npx] for gap + strips `style.gap` | pixels for gap |
| `set_display` | `props.className` (display/grid classes) | Tailwind tokens |
| `set_submit` | `props.type` = `"submit"` or null | boolean |
| `set_input_props` | `props.type`, `props.step`, `props.multiline`, etc. | typed values |
| `set_animation` | `node.animation.*` object | enum strings matching panel |

**Runtime rendering note:** Arbitrary-value Tailwind classes written from JSON (e.g. `pt-[96px]`, `bg-[#0f172a]`) are not compiled by NativeWind's static scanner. The renderer's `classToInlineStyle()` function in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx` converts them to inline styles at render time. This means the JSON stores classes (for panel sync) while the browser sees inline styles (for correct rendering). `props.style` values take precedence over `classToInlineStyle` output.

