## How the System Prompt Is Built

`buildKnowledge(context)` is called per-request and returns the full system prompt string. It injects:

- `paletteSnapshot` — live resolved CSS variable values (var=hex pairs) so the AI knows the current theme
- `currentPageName`, `pages`, `selectedNodeSummary` — per-request builder state
- Component list (auto-derived from `PRIMITIVE_COMPONENTS`)
- Component structure reference (from `aiRef` field on each primitive)
- All tool descriptions, quick reference, formula functions

**Injection order:**
```
1. Project context (appName, description, category, mood)
2. Contrast Rule
3. Builder Context (current page, selected node)
4. Core Philosophy (no raw Tailwind, no set_class)
5. Tool Strategy (build incrementally, pre-assign IDs)
6. Section building patterns and examples
7. Width/Height sizing model
8. Quick reference table
9. Component list (auto-generated)
10. Component structure reference (from aiRef)
11. Formula function library (auto-generated)
12. Tool reference table
```

**Never hardcode theme values** — they come from `paletteSnapshot` at runtime.

